        <p>Now let's consider carefully how the pattern should continue in the product column. First, the column is labeled <q>product,</q> so we need to stick with multiplication. Second, it would be great if we could still use repeated multiplication for negative integer exponents. Last, we know that dividing the value by <m>2</m> is equivalent to multiplying the value by <m>\frac{1}{2}</m>. So we have:</p>

